snippet: The New York senator is mired near the bottom of most polls but hopes to jump-start her campaign and fund-raising as she aggressively criticizes anti-abortion laws in Alabama and other states.
lead_paragraph: In the two years leading up to her 2020 run, Senator Kirsten Gillibrand spent millions of dollars building up a network of online and grass-roots donors who could power her coming presidential campaign.
abstract: The New York senator is mired near the bottom of most polls but hopes to jump-start her campaign and fund-raising as she aggressively criticizes anti-abortion laws in Alabama and other states.

snippet: The newest debate among the Democratic presidential candidates is whether accepting an invitation from Fox News is a Faustian bargain.
lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host.
abstract: The newest debate among the Democratic presidential candidates is whether accepting an invitation from Fox News is a Faustian bargain.

snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio, in announcing his campaign, described his city as “legendarily tough and big and complicated.” In their response, New Yorkers proved just how apt that was.

headline_main: What to Know About Pacific Gas & Electric’s Role in the Camp Fire

snippet: In a new report, Democrats and Republicans denounced the “tough on crime” approach as unsparingly as they once promoted it.
lead_paragraph: One contributor to a new report on American criminal justice called the current system “an affront to our most fundamental values of freedom, equality and liberty,” then suggested sentencing fewer people to prison, sealing nonviolent criminal records and restoring voting rights for released offenders.
abstract: In a new report, Democrats and Republicans denounced the “tough on crime” approach as unsparingly as they once promoted it.

headline_main: Left and Right Agree on Criminal Justice: They Were Both Wrong Before
headline_print_headline: On This Issue, Both Sides  Concede They Were Wrong

snippet: Barring legal challenges, a new Alabama law would effectively outlaw abortions in the state. “This is a war on women,” Senator Kirsten Gillibrand said.
lead_paragraph: For Senator Elizabeth Warren, the moment brought up memories of “back alley butchers” and “desperate women.” Senator Kamala Harris compared it to “a scene from ‘The Handmaid’s Tale.’” And Senator Kirsten Gillibrand warned about a “war on women,” calling for Americans to “fight like hell.”
abstract: Barring legal challenges, a new Alabama law would effectively outlaw abortions in the state. “This is a war on women,” Senator Kirsten Gillibrand said.

snippet: Mr. Castro’s sweeping plan would also eliminate tuition at public universities and community colleges and overhaul the student-debt repayment process.
lead_paragraph: Julián Castro, whose campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination has so far struggled to gain much momentum, unveiled a proposal Monday to create a national, federally funded prekindergarten program, eliminate tuition at public universities and community colleges and alter the student-debt repayment process, part of a sweeping policy plan that his campaign hopes could reshape public education.
abstract: Mr. Castro’s sweeping plan would also eliminate tuition at public universities and community colleges and overhaul the student-debt repayment process.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Uber Bombed. Now What?

snippet: The nation’s first presidential caucus is always important, but with more than 20 Democrats running this time, the need for a strong showing is far more urgent.
lead_paragraph: IOWA CITY — It may be nearly nine months until the first balloting of the 2020 primary, but candidates are already practically tripping over one another in Iowa.
abstract: The nation’s first presidential caucus is always important, but with more than 20 Democrats running this time, the need for a strong showing is far more urgent.
